<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D47FFE6FFBA48D8CBFEFD39C613" authority="Kóbor, 2019" authorityName="Kóbor" authorityYear="2019" box="[470,727,1516,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Umbrageocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kondorosyi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B93EEAD6FFE6FFBA48D8CBFEFD39C613" box="[470,727,1516,1537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Umbrageocoris kondorosyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D57ADFFE6FFBA4BD3CBFEFCF8C613" box="[733,790,1516,1537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from different angles
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF536C4FFE7FFBB49A0CEAFFC58C27E" blockId="5.[174,1128,189,620]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
that more authors consider the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D47FFE7FFBB4B72CEACFD33C0CA" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1814" box="[636,733,190,216]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Geocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAD6FFE7FFBB4B72CEACFD33C0CA" box="[636,733,190,216]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Geocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“an ill­defined group of species belonging to perhaps several distinct genera” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB4B35FFE7FFBB4BE3CECDFC1BC0EB" author="READIO, J. &amp; SWEET, M. H." box="[749,1013,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref3756" refString="READIO, J. &amp; SWEET, M. H. (1982): A review of the Geocorinae of the United States east of 100 th meridian (Hemiptera: Lygaeidae). - Entomological Society of America Miscellaneous Publications 12. 92 pp." type="book" year="1982">READIO &amp; SWEET 1982</bibRefCitation>
, MALIPA- TIL 1994) which is in need of a thorough revision. Based on the literature avail- able and own observation, the author of recent study supports this opinion and concludes that the given combination of characters is eligible to separate this taxon on generic level from other members of New Guinean fauna. One of the most convincing characters is the arrangement and shape of the outer structures of metathoracic scent efferent apparatus (
<figureCitation id="13712A41FFE7FFBB4A3CCFBBFC96C1D1" box="[818,888,425,451]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,210,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[178,1126,1203,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-400@5.[174,1127,1203,1468]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 4. Peritreme of metathoracic scent gland in New Guinean Geocorinae: A = Germalus Stål, 1862; B = Umbrageocoris gen. n.; C = Geocoris Fallén, 1814. Legend: cx2 = mesocoxa, ev =" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734684" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5734684/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), which is showing remarkable differences if compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D47FFE7FFBB4B93CFD9FD10C1F7" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1814" box="[669,766,459,485]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Geocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAD6FFE7FFBB4B93CFD9FD10C1F7" box="[669,766,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Geocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D47FFE7FFBB4A4CCFD8FBFCC1F6" box="[834,1042,458,484]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Germalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93EEAD6FFE7FFBB4A4CCFD8FC5EC1F6" box="[834,944,458,484]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Germalus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
of the region. Based on the results of recent study and unpublished findings of the author this character might have significant value in taxonomy and phylog- eny of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D47FFE7FFBB480CCC3DFE7DC25B" box="[258,403,559,585]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geocoridae</taxonomicName>
. Similar findings were concluded by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB4B35FFE7FFBB4A53CC22FF17C279" author="KMENT, P. &amp; VILIMOVA, J." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 59" refId="ref3375" refString="KMENT, P. &amp; VILIMOVA, J. (2010): Thoracic scent efferent system of the Tessaratomidae sen- su lato (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Pentatomoidea) with implication to the phylogeny of the family. - Zootaxa 2363: 1 - 59. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2363.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">KMENT and VILIMOVÁ (2010)</bibRefCitation>
in family 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D47FFE7FFBB4878CC43FDD9C279" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1864" box="[374,567,593,619]" class="Insecta" family="Tessaratomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tessaratomidae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D47FFE7FFBB4B48CC43FD0EC279" box="[582,736,593,619]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heteroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Heteroptera</taxonomicName>
: Pentatomoidea).
</paragraph>
